cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Gaia DR3 NSS substellar candidate mining pipeline + tentative-candidate list"
message: "If you use this pipeline or the tentative-candidate list in your research, please cite the Zenodo DOI (auto-generated per release) and this GitHub repository."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Alejandro"
    family-names: "Zarco"
    alias: "alejandrozarco"
    email: "alejandro.zarcos@gmail.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/alejandrozarco/gaia-dr3-substellar-novelty-search"
abstract: >-
  An archival filter-cascade pipeline that cross-correlates Gaia DR3
  Non-Single-Star (NSS) Orbital and Acceleration tables against 30+ public
  literature catalogs and archival radial-velocity time-series. The pipeline
  identifies candidate substellar (13-80 M_J) companions to bright nearby
  stars (V < 12, d < 200 pc) that have not been claimed in published
  companion catalogs. After applying ~28 sequential filters (including
  conditional RUWE per NSS solution_type, HGCA Brandt 2024 chi-squared
  tier filtering, proper-motion-corrected exoplanet.eu coord cross-match
  at 10 arcsec radius (v8), Halbwachs FluxRatio + direct-method M_2,
  both-estimates-stellar M_2 rejection, and the Gaia DR3 documented
  false-positive list), the pipeline produces a list of 10 tentative
  substellar candidates. None are confirmed by independent orbital
  characterization. Status is experimental archival mining; confirmation
  requires Gaia DR4 (Dec 2026 expected) or new ground-based RV
  observations.
keywords:
  - "Gaia DR3"
  - "non-single stars"
  - "brown dwarfs"
  - "substellar companions"
  - "astrometric binaries"
  - "Hipparcos-Gaia proper motion anomaly"
  - "filter cascade"
  - "tentative candidate"
license: "CC-BY-4.0"
version: "1.9.0"
date-released: "2026-05-17"
